data.name: TextBox4.Text
data.value:
If you get stuck and need help.
1. Click the Obsidian TTRPG Tutorials link above. 2. Click the Join Obsidian TTRPG Community Discord -- This is where the majority of the TTRPG Community are hiding. Come join us! 3. In the Ask A Questions section create a new post. 4. Include: -- screenshot of your bin folder. -- copy of your config file. -- copy of the command you are using to run the CLI. -- copy of any errors you are getting.

data.name: TextBox3.Text
data.value:
If you are using Fantasy Statblocks then you need to:
Obsidian Vault > Settings > Community Plugins > Fantasy Statblocks > Options -- Automatically Parse Frontmatter for Creates == ON -- Bestiary Folder: Add the Compendium and Rules folders. Remove the / from the list.
If you are using Initiative Tracker then you need to: Obsidian Vault > Settings > Community Plugins > Initiative Tracker > Options -- Sync Monsters from TTRPG Statblocks == ON
Restart your vault to trigger the parser which will make everything work.

data.name: TextBox1.Text
data.value:
The first time you complete this process you should click the Auto Download buttons to download the data sources. In the future, you dont need to click those buttons each time, instead click the Update buttons to check for the latest copies of each data and then move onto the Create Config File tab to create.modify your config file. The tool will remember your settings if you close it.
Once everything is installed correctly it should look something like this...
Install Folder/5etools-src Install Folder/5etools-img Install Folder/examples/templates/tools5e/<templates> Install Folder/docs Install Folder/default Install Folder/homebrew/ Install Folder/My.Config.File.json Install Folder/ttrpg-convert.exe Install Folder/templates_examples.zip Install Folder/ttrpg-convert-cli-X.X.X-windows-x86_64
If you are manually downloading the data you need to extract everything into a similar folder structure.
